title: The Return of The Dream Syndicate
content: Celebrity News June 02, 2018 The Return of The Dream Syndicate Chris Sikich The Dream Syndicate is back with their first new studio record since 1988! The album is called “How Did I Find Myself Here?” Bandmates Steve Wynn, Dennis Duck, Mark Walton and Jason Victor have been performing the new songs from the record, and classics like “The Days of Wine and Roses,” for fans around the world. “Extra’s” Senior Music Correspondent Adam Weissler caught up with Wynn at L.A.’s famed Troubadour before a recent show, where they talked about the new music and much more. “Extra” was at the Troubadour as The Dream Syndicate performed “Glide” during a soundcheck. Watch! Be sure to check out their Record Store Day 2018 special release “How We Found Ourselves... Everywhere!” on digital platforms June 22, and visit TheDreamSyndicate.com for tour dates and more. #Music#AsSeenOnExtra Comments Around the Web More In Celebrity News Chris Sikich Celebrity News The Return of The Dream Syndicate Getty Images CELEBRITY NEWS Benedict Cumberbatch: Hero in Real-Life Mugging Getty Images WEDDING NEWS Brody Jenner & Kaitlynn Carter Got Married!
